The preferred #Layer2 solution is via rollups. They bundle hundreds of txs into a single #Layer1 tx.

The tx are executed outside of #Ethereum but the data is posted to the main chain ensuring security and finality. 6/12

This enables #ETH to do what it's good at settling transaction in a decentralized and secure manner.

Whilst allowing #Layer2 to handle the workload of an increased number of faster and cheaper transactions. 5/12

#Layer2 solutions attempt solve the scalability (speed/cost) challenge whilst maintaining decentralization and security
